# React Frontend

## Components

- Functional components and hooks only.
- Colocate component, styles, and tests in the same directory.

## API access

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — fetch in a component
const res = await fetch(`${url}/items`);

// ✅ GOOD — use the api client layer
import { listItems } from '@/api/items';
const items = await listItems();
```

All HTTP calls go through `frontend/src/api/`. Backend URLs come from config (`import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL`), never hardcoded in components.

## Async UI

Every async operation needs loading and error states.

## Styling

Use CSS modules (`Component.module.css`) unless the project documents otherwise. Global tokens live in `frontend/src/styles/`.

## Platform APIs

Storage, notifications, and device info go through `frontend/src/platform/` — never call `window`, `localStorage`, or `navigator` directly from components.

Adjust path globs if the frontend directory differs (e.g. `web/**/*.{ts,tsx}`).
